info.name: SnapSwap RKYC API with mocking endpoints
info.description:

request.description:
Endpoint to ask for Dossier delivery. Delivery in essence is Dossier data with AML checks. In the Portal we call this endpoint when consistency flag in the Dossier status is true. We issue this twice, one for LIMITED dossier and one for BASIC dossier.

**References**

Check the following classes:

- SnapSwapJobType#DELIVER_DOSSIER
- SnapSwapDossierDeliveryService

request.description:
**This is Mock specific endpoint.**

Deliver Dossier to Portal endpoint. You must submit LIMITED and BASIC as a separate requests. You can differentiate between LIMITED and BASIC using 1.2. endpoint.

**Reference**

Check the following classes:

- SnapSwapDossierDeliveryEndpointController

**This is Mock specific endpoint.**

Use this endpoint to change satuses of various entries of Dossier. Change "type" and "status" and do not touch "dossierId". Differentiate between LIMITED and BASIC by using 1.2. endpoint.

The following "type" is supported:

- phone - relevant for LIMITED
- email - relevant for LIMITED
- residential_address - relevant for LIMITED
- enterprise - relevant for LIMITED
- consistency - relevant for LIMITED and BASIC
- delivery - relevant for LIMITED and BASIC
- id_document - relevant for LIMITED
- residential_address_document - relevant for LIMITED
- document_questions - relevant for BASIC
- questions - relevant for BASIC. Might be for LIMITED, but not sure
- tax_id - relevant for BASIC
    

For "status" you can use any option which is defined in RKYC specification, but in the Portal we care about two:

- success
- failure
    

**Reference**

Check the following classes:

- SnapSwapDossierDeliveryEndpointController

**This is Mock specific endpoint.**

Allows to add "failure" entry to Dossier. If some of the Dossier entries have status "failure" then there is a separate entry "failure" which provides more details about the failure. Check the body for examples.

We had [https://wallee.atlassian.net/browse/WAL-91391](https://wallee.atlassian.net/browse/WAL-91391) issue where SnapSwap responded with "failure" entry for delivery and we didn't support that and case was stuck.

**This is Mock specific endpoint.**

Normally you loose whole state when you stop Mock application. This endpoint allows to save state to a file. Then when you start the app again you can use "Restore state" endpoint and load the state from a file.

**This is Mock specific endpoint.**

You can restore app state from the file.
